import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['normal'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Normal Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'normal' values in the dataset?")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['actual'], label='Actual')
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['forecast'], label='Forecast')
    
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Values')
    plt.title("How do the 'actual' values compare to the 'forecast' values?")
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    id_counts = data['id'].value_counts()
    id_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('ID')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'id' values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
